Enyalioides sophiarothschildae is known from the northeastern slopes of the Cordillera Central in Peru between 1600-1700 m (Fig. 3). This species is only known from two adjacent localities, the trail to La Cueva-Anasco Pueblo in the drainage of the Lejia river and El Dorado in the drainage of the Blanco river, both tributaries of the Huallabamba river in the northern part of the Huallaga river basin. This area corresponds to the Selva Alta (400-1000 m) and Yungas (300-2300 m) ecoregions ( Brack 1986 ;
Penaherrera del Aguila 1989
).
